  "narrative": {
    "intro": "Service-Disabled Veteran-Owned Small Business (SDVOSB) set-aside contracts totaled $5.7B in FY2026 to date. There were 11,891 awards with an average award size of $481K, and obligations fell 34.2% year over year. The Department of Veterans Affairs accounted for the largest share of FY2026 to date obligations at $4.6B, with the Department of Defense at $556M and other agencies contributing smaller amounts. Top vendor recipients included V3GATE, LLC at $324M, FOUR POINTS TECHNOLOGY, L.L.C. at $215M, and SPREZZATURA MANAGEMENT CONSULTING, LLC at $214M. Industry concentration is notable in construction and IT categories, led by Commercial and Institutional Building Construction at $1.5B and Other Computer Related Services at $1.2B, followed by Custom Computer Programming Services at $434M. Historical obligations show a peak in FY23 at $9.1B and lower totals in FY24 and FY25 at $8.8B and $8.7B respectively, before the FY26 to date figure of $5.7B. All figures are contract obligations; current-year totals are partial (fiscal year to date).",
    "sections": [
      {
        "heading": "What is the current size and recent trend of SDVOSB set-aside obligations?",
        "body": "Total SDVOSB set-aside obligations are $5.7B in FY2026 to date, with 11,891 awards and an average award size of $481K. Obligations are down 34.2% year over year. FY26 to date follows FY25 at $8.7B, FY24 at $8.8B, and a FY23 peak of $9.1B. These figures are contract obligations and the FY2026 total is fiscal year to date."
      },
      {
        "heading": "Which agencies, vendors, and industries account for the largest shares of SDVOSB obligations?",
        "body": "The Department of Veterans Affairs is the largest buying agency at $4.6B, followed by the Department of Defense at $556M and the Department of Homeland Security at $113M. Leading vendors are V3GATE, LLC at $324M, FOUR POINTS TECHNOLOGY, L.L.C. at $215M, and SPREZZATURA MANAGEMENT CONSULTING, LLC at $214M. Top industry categories are Commercial and Institutional Building Construction at $1.5B and Other Computer Related Services at $1.2B."
      }
    ]
  },
  "faq": [
    {
      "q": "How much does the federal government award through SDVOSB set-asides?",
      "a": "The federal government awarded $5.7B through SDVOSB set-asides in FY2026 to date. There were 11,891 awards with an average award size of $481K, and obligations are down 34.2% year over year. Historical annual obligations include FY25 at $8.7B, FY24 at $8.8B, FY23 at $9.1B, FY22 at $8B, and FY21 at $7.2B."
    },
    {
      "q": "Which agencies use SDVOSB set-asides the most?",
      "a": "The Department of Veterans Affairs uses SDVOSB set-asides the most, with $4.6B in FY2026 to date obligations. Other top buying agencies for FY2026 to date are the Department of Defense at $556M and the Department of Homeland Security at $113M, with additional contributions from HHS at $96.1M and DOT at $68.3M."
    },
